The paper deals with cooperative game theory and its application to ride-sharing services, which falls under the category of cs.GT (Game Theory). The use of the Shapley value also suggests a connection to machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The efficient computation of the Shapley value involves algorithms and data structures, which are relevant to computer science theory (cs.DS). The simulations conducted in the paper also involve statistical analysis and machine learning techniques, which could fall under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
